1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,500
[MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:01:01,150 --> 00:01:02,640
[CLOCK CHIMES]

3
00:01:32,580 --> 00:01:35,080
[DOG BARKING AND HOWLING]

4
00:01:59,530 --> 00:02:01,530
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

5
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,260
But how else can we explain
these terrible deaths?

6
00:02:17,260 --> 00:02:19,740
Von Ilse last night.

7
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:21,160
Five others before him.

8
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:23,890
That's six within as
many weeks, Inspector.

9
00:02:23,890 --> 00:02:27,820
Our friends, neighbors that
we've known for years, drained

10
00:02:27,820 --> 00:02:29,730
Of their life's
blood, found dead

11
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:33,130
In bed, likely skeletons
of skin and bone.

12
00:02:33,130 --> 00:02:36,990
Vampires are at large,
I tell you, vampires!

13
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:40,430
Yeah, malignant demons who
issue forth from their graves

14
00:02:40,430 --> 00:02:42,790
In the dead of night
to attack their victims

15
00:02:42,790 --> 00:02:45,280
And drink the blood
from their veins.

16
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,160
Brr!

17
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:47,910
God in heaven,
Brettschneider, don't jest!

18
00:02:47,910 --> 00:02:51,290
Ah, that blood-sucking legend
belongs in the same category

19
00:02:51,290 --> 00:02:54,040
With werewolves and all
other peasant superstitions.

20
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:55,460
But the bats, man!

21
00:02:55,460 --> 00:02:56,890
The bats!

22
00:02:56,890 --> 00:02:57,840
God, yes!

23
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,540
Big ones, so!

24
00:02:59,540 --> 00:03:01,550
Oh, now we're
switching to bats again.

25
00:03:01,550 --> 00:03:06,850
There was an epidemic of giant
bats in Klineschloss in 1643.

26
00:03:06,850 --> 00:03:10,440
And at the same time, there
was an outbreak of vampirism.

27
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,710
Rot!

28
00:03:11,710 --> 00:03:14,520
Why, this record from the
town archives proves it.

29
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:16,510
Says it, not proves it.

30
00:03:16,510 --> 00:03:18,510
Well, I'll show you.

31
00:03:18,510 --> 00:03:20,490
I'll show you.

32
00:03:20,490 --> 00:03:23,340
Now, ah, here it is.

33
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:26,120
"And on this day was
von Hausmen hanged"

34
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:28,150
From a gibbet in
the public square

35
00:03:28,150 --> 00:03:31,820
After being convicted on a
proven charge of vampirism.

36
00:03:31,820 --> 00:03:34,910
And on this same day, there
did occur the departure

37
00:03:34,910 --> 00:03:38,100
Of the bats, thousands of
horrible flying creatures

38
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:40,490
Which infested the
town for weeks.

39
00:03:40,490 --> 00:03:41,680
And on the night
of this same day,

40
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:47,290
February 13 in the year of our
Lord, 1643, was there a stake

41
00:03:47,290 --> 00:03:49,480
Driven through von
Hausmen's heart

42
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:53,020
"And his head cut off with
a gravedigger's shovel."

43
00:03:53,020 --> 00:03:53,930
There.

44
00:03:53,930 --> 00:03:55,430
Well, all the
records in the world

45
00:03:55,430 --> 00:03:57,670
Can't make me
believe in vampires.

46
00:03:57,670 --> 00:03:59,980
There are bloodsucking
bats, yes,

47
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:02,180
In South America, thousands
of miles from here.

48
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:03,840
But not in Klineschloss.

49
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,210
But bats fly!

50
00:04:05,210 --> 00:04:06,880
They could fly here!

51
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:09,950
You saw the
buggers, all of them.

52
00:04:09,950 --> 00:04:13,140
Two wounds on the neck,
right at the jugular vein.

53
00:04:13,140 --> 00:04:15,290
Two wounds on the neck,
pierced and spread apart

54
00:04:15,290 --> 00:04:17,360
Just as if two
fang-like teeth had

55
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:21,620
Bitten through the flesh
and right into the veins.

56
00:04:21,620 --> 00:04:26,620
And in every case, a blood clot,
eight inches from the victim's

57
00:04:26,620 --> 00:04:31,810
Neck, the mark of the feast,
the devil's signature.

58
00:04:31,810 --> 00:04:35,600
Does that appear the mark of
a human being or a demon's?

59
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:40,030
God save us, the devil's.

60
00:04:40,030 --> 00:04:43,110
You ought to make a pretty
fair meal for a vampire.

61
00:04:43,110 --> 00:04:45,270
But let's be consistent.

62
00:04:45,270 --> 00:04:49,340
Are these human
vampires or... or bats?

63
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:51,980
Vampires can take the
shape of a human or a bat,

64
00:04:51,980 --> 00:04:53,200
Just as they choose.

65
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:54,280
Oh.

66
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:57,050
They're magicians.

67
00:04:57,050 --> 00:04:58,940
Well, it doesn't
make sense to me.

68
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:01,180
The whole village is in terror.

69
00:05:01,180 --> 00:05:05,130
We live in closed houses,
behind locked doors and bolted

70
00:05:05,130 --> 00:05:08,090
Shutters, not daring
to close our eyes,

71
00:05:08,090 --> 00:05:12,640
Fearful lest this unseen, silent
death may find us in our sleep.

72
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:17,940
For it is then that it strikes,
swiftly, silently, ghastly.

73
00:05:17,940 --> 00:05:20,010
My room is tightly closed.

74
00:05:20,010 --> 00:05:22,870
The windows are
barred, nailed down!

75
00:05:22,870 --> 00:05:25,800
Nothing can get in, nothing!

76
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:29,080
But they tell me vampires
can go through stone walls,

77
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:30,220
Like that.

78
00:05:30,220 --> 00:05:32,890
God save me, so they can!

79
00:05:32,890 --> 00:05:35,210
We've got to do
something, I tell you!

80
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:38,290
Klineschloss will become
a deserted village.

81
00:05:38,290 --> 00:05:40,350
Well, you might
capture all the bats

82
00:05:40,350 --> 00:05:41,490
And drown them in the river.

83
00:05:41,490 --> 00:05:42,190
Karl!

84
00:05:42,190 --> 00:05:42,890
Karl!

85
00:05:42,890 --> 00:05:44,950
While you're hunting for
vampires and chasing bats,

86
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:47,520
I'm looking for a human
being, a murderer, a thief!

87
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:48,810
Well then, don't jest about it.

88
00:05:48,810 --> 00:05:49,510
Do something!

89
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:51,040
I'm trying to!

90
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:54,020
Every hour, every day, every
night since this thing started!

91
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:56,430
[DOG BARKING AND HOWLING]

92
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:03,680
Do you hear it?

93
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,650
Yes!

94
00:06:04,650 --> 00:06:06,090
Yes!

95
00:06:06,090 --> 00:06:11,620
Night after night, lying
awake until dawn, waiting!

96
00:06:11,620 --> 00:06:13,270
For what?

97
00:06:13,270 --> 00:06:15,700
I don't know.

98
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:16,600
That's what I thought.

99
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:22,240
Good night, gentlemen.

100
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:24,220
Don't let the vampires get you.

101
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:05,680
[POP]

102
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:06,380
[LAUGHS]

103
00:07:06,380 --> 00:07:09,090
Are your kisses dynamite!

104
00:07:09,090 --> 00:07:10,360
Don't you like my kisses?

105
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:19,620
Well, how's my
mastermind this evening.

106
00:07:19,620 --> 00:07:22,360
Well, if you want the
truth, not so good.

107
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:24,400
The Burgermeister
and his grand council

108
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,060
Still stick to the
vampire theory, huh?

109
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:27,020
Stick to it?

110
00:07:27,020 --> 00:07:27,720
Ha!

111
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:30,900
They're quoting
history to prove it.

112
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:32,650
I think you and Dr. von
Niemang are the only

113
00:07:32,650 --> 00:07:34,060
Sane people left in the village.

114
00:07:34,060 --> 00:07:34,760
And you?

115
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:35,460
What about you?

116
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:36,690
Hmm, me.

117
00:07:36,690 --> 00:07:38,270
Well, I'm beginning
to think I'm seven

118
00:07:38,270 --> 00:07:40,790
Different kinds of a fool.

119
00:07:40,790 --> 00:07:44,520
Murders are being done
under my very nose.

120
00:07:44,520 --> 00:07:47,440
I must be as blind as
the bats themselves.

121
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:49,010
I can't find a single clue.

122
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:50,550
Oh, but you will,
Karl, you will.

123
00:07:50,550 --> 00:07:51,620
Well, I haven't.

124
00:07:51,620 --> 00:07:52,550
AUNT GUSSIE: Oh, Ruth!

125
00:07:57,660 --> 00:08:02,060
And here comes dear Aunt Gussie
to spread good cheer and hope.

126
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:05,030
Just what I thought,
slaving your life away

127
00:08:05,030 --> 00:08:06,020
In this awful place.

128
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:09,980
It hasn't got that nice, plain,
wholesome smell of a hospital.

129
00:08:09,980 --> 00:08:11,460
How are you, Karl?

130
00:08:11,460 --> 00:08:12,950
Oh, quite well, thank you.

131
00:08:12,950 --> 00:08:13,960
Well, I'm not.

132
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:16,810
This clammy old place is
bound to give me pericarditis,

133
00:08:16,810 --> 00:08:19,310
[INAUDIBLE], neuritis,
[INAUDIBLE]...

134
00:08:19,310 --> 00:08:20,990
Well anyway, Ruth.

135
00:08:20,990 --> 00:08:21,940
You want some coffee?

136
00:08:21,940 --> 00:08:23,840
No, no thank you,
Frau Schappmann.

137
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:24,560
Well, just as well.

138
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:25,750
There's only two cups.

139
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:27,180
Here, dear.

140
00:08:27,180 --> 00:08:28,280
Anything to chill
out your bones.

141
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:29,170
Thank you.

142
00:08:29,170 --> 00:08:30,960
Speaking of chills,
Frau Schappmann,

143
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:32,260
Did you know the
villagers are supposed

144
00:08:32,260 --> 00:08:34,440
To be infested with
ghouls and vampires?

145
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:35,330
Oh, Karl!

146
00:08:35,330 --> 00:08:38,020
Vampires!

147
00:08:38,020 --> 00:08:41,170
Pariahs among fiends,
demoniacal creatures

148
00:08:41,170 --> 00:08:44,160
With huge canine
teeth who bite deeply

149
00:08:44,160 --> 00:08:46,850
Into the necks of
their victims, to quaff

150
00:08:46,850 --> 00:08:50,920
And gorge on blood,
warm human blood!

151
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:53,400
There's no such thing as a
vampire, Karl Brettschneider.

152
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,420
I don't believe in it.

153
00:08:54,420 --> 00:08:56,640
You're just saying
that to frighten me.

154
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,680
And I just won't be frightened.

155
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:01,190
I'm entirely too sensible
to believe in such rubbish.

156
00:09:01,190 --> 00:09:02,060
I beg pardon.

157
00:09:02,060 --> 00:09:04,180
[GASPS] Oh, that was you.

158
00:09:04,180 --> 00:09:06,070
I'm sorry if I frightened you.

159
00:09:06,070 --> 00:09:07,760
Who said you frightened me?

160
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:09,570
I'm not afraid of anything.

161
00:09:09,570 --> 00:09:11,160
Could you tell me where
Dr. von Niemann is?

162
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:12,650
Well, he drove to
the village to see

163
00:09:12,650 --> 00:09:14,150
Martha, the old apple woman.

164
00:09:14,150 --> 00:09:15,140
Thank you.

165
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:44,650
Is this what Dr.
Hobb prescribed?

166
00:09:44,650 --> 00:09:45,950
Yes, sir.

167
00:09:45,950 --> 00:09:49,300
She takes it in water.

168
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:50,660
Hmm.

169
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:53,150
Well, continue giving it to her.

170
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:54,140
Yes, sir.

171
00:10:22,530 --> 00:10:24,460
It's stifiling in here.

172
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:26,250
Open these windows.

173
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:27,590
Herman open windows.

174
00:10:27,590 --> 00:10:29,090
Me do, me do.

175
00:10:36,490 --> 00:10:40,930
[SIGH] Well, she'll
sleep well now, poor soul.

176
00:10:40,930 --> 00:10:43,090
It won't be necessary
for you to stay here.

177
00:10:43,090 --> 00:10:45,520
A good night's sleep will
work wonders for her.

178
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:47,460
It was kind of you
to come, Doctor.

179
00:10:47,460 --> 00:10:52,640
Oh, Martha has sold me
apples for many years,

180
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,800
Always the good,
ripe, juicy ones.

181
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:56,580
Martha give me apples!

182
00:10:56,580 --> 00:10:57,550
I like!

183
00:10:57,550 --> 00:10:59,000
[LAUGHS]

184
00:10:59,000 --> 00:10:59,970
Shh!

185
00:10:59,970 --> 00:11:02,010
Oh, to think.

186
00:11:02,010 --> 00:11:03,880
[MOANS]

187
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:05,490
DR. VON NIEMANN:
She wants her cross.

188
00:11:05,490 --> 00:11:06,470
Herman get.

189
00:11:06,470 --> 00:11:07,450
Herman get.

190
00:11:07,450 --> 00:11:08,220
Here.

191
00:11:08,220 --> 00:11:08,920
Here.

192
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:11,370
Now that for Martha.

193
00:11:11,370 --> 00:11:12,630
There.

194
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:13,330
Oh!

195
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:18,250
She won't let it
out of her sight.

196
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:20,230
A terrible experience.

197
00:11:20,230 --> 00:11:22,490
To be attacked by a giant
bat is enough to shatter

198
00:11:22,490 --> 00:11:23,970
Anyone's nerves.

199
00:11:23,970 --> 00:11:27,900
She talks about it all the
time, how it flew in her face

200
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:29,860
And tried to sink its
teeth in her throat.

201
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:30,850
No, no, no, no.

202
00:11:30,850 --> 00:11:33,300
Bats no do!

203
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:37,130
They soft, like cat.

204
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:38,100
They not bite Herman!

205
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:39,520
[CRIES OUT]

206
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:41,900
[INAUDIBLE] see
what you've done?

207
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:42,860
There, there.

208
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:43,810
There, Martha, there.

209
00:11:43,810 --> 00:11:44,760
Shh.

210
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,190
[CRYING SLOWS]

211
00:11:48,740 --> 00:11:50,480
She'll be all right.

212
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:53,310
If she isn't, let me know.

213
00:11:53,310 --> 00:11:54,780
Thank you for coming, Doctor.

214
00:11:54,780 --> 00:11:56,050
That's all right.

215
00:11:56,050 --> 00:11:56,750
Goodnight.

216
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:57,450
Goodnight.

217
00:12:00,190 --> 00:12:01,670
Run along, Herman.

218
00:12:01,670 --> 00:12:03,430
You can see Martha tomorrow.

219
00:12:03,430 --> 00:12:04,130
Oh.

220
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:23,500
Ah, Dr. von Niemann.

221
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:24,950
Ah, Kringen, how are you?

222
00:12:24,950 --> 00:12:26,810
Much better, thank
you kindly sir,

223
00:12:26,810 --> 00:12:27,770
Since you prescribed for me.

224
00:12:27,770 --> 00:12:30,390
That's right.

225
00:12:30,390 --> 00:12:31,950
Go to bed, Herman.

226
00:12:31,950 --> 00:12:32,840
Go to bed!

227
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,270
You shouldn't be filing
around the streets.

228
00:12:34,270 --> 00:12:35,130
It's dangerous!

229
00:12:35,130 --> 00:12:37,990
Oh.

230
00:12:37,990 --> 00:12:39,230
I'm afraid.

231
00:12:39,230 --> 00:12:40,260
Afraid?

232
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:41,810
Afraid of what, Kringen?

233
00:12:41,810 --> 00:12:43,290
The bats, sir.

234
00:12:43,290 --> 00:12:46,990
Big giant bats, with
wings like an eagle.

235
00:12:46,990 --> 00:12:49,010
DR. VON NIEMANN: You
saw this bat, you say?

236
00:12:49,010 --> 00:12:50,870
I saw it swooping
down the street.

237
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:53,030
It came directly
for my throat, sir.

238
00:12:53,030 --> 00:12:54,480
When was this, Kringen?

239
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:57,130
Last night when they
came to take von Ilse.

240
00:12:57,130 --> 00:12:58,650
It was a big, monstrous thing.

241
00:12:58,650 --> 00:13:02,310
I saw it leap across the
alley and into a window.

242
00:13:02,310 --> 00:13:04,530
I ran just as fast as
my legs could carry me.

243
00:13:04,530 --> 00:13:05,970
You said nothing about this?

244
00:13:05,970 --> 00:13:09,040
There's enough fear
in the village already.

245
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:10,970
Maybe I should.

246
00:13:10,970 --> 00:13:13,940
Maybe I sh... I will.

247
00:13:13,940 --> 00:13:14,870
I'll tell the Burgermeister.

248
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:16,070
Yes, Kringen.

249
00:13:16,070 --> 00:13:16,840
That's the thing to do.

250
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:18,720
No!

251
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:22,350
Bats... bats good!

252
00:13:22,350 --> 00:13:24,480
They not hurt Herman.

253
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:25,910
He plays with them.

254
00:13:25,910 --> 00:13:27,410
You... you no tell!

255
00:13:27,410 --> 00:13:28,110
No.

256
00:13:28,110 --> 00:13:31,210
No, no, no, go to bed, Herman.

257
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:32,380
Go on.

258
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:33,080
Go on, go to bed!

259
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:39,590
You say he plays with bats?

260
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:41,610
His garret is filled with them.

261
00:13:41,610 --> 00:13:43,930
He makes pets of them.

262
00:13:43,930 --> 00:13:45,740
That's odd.

263
00:13:45,740 --> 00:13:46,730
Very odd.

264
00:13:46,730 --> 00:13:53,600
Maybe... maybe he's it.

265
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:56,400
Herman prowls around the
streets all hours of the night,

266
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,090
Just like an animal.

